  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d85\u0d82\u0dc1\u0dba\u0dda \u0dad\u0db1\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dbb \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca \u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Anura Parliament questions about the positions of the President's media department",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "MP Anura Kumara Dissanayaka questioned the current President Ranil Wickramasinghe's media department in Parliament today.",
        "He said that the Presidential Media Division has a staff of 15 directors, 10 deputy directors, 8 photographers, 4 video editors, and 6 media assistants, as well as the Presidential Adviser, the Director General of the Presidential Media.",
        "\"Mr. President Ranil Wickramasinghe went to the village and told those who are not working to go home. How many directors are there in the media unit? If the president can come to the parliament and tell how many media unit he has?",
        "It has been one and a half months now. What are their jobs? What is the salary paid to them? If not, send them home. Now he is telling the public servants to go home. Remember, he was the one who sent all the government employees home together. See how the presidential secretariat is filled today. Don't tell this to the country.\""
      ],
